Arsenal have released their squad that will tackle Burnley in today’s Premier League fixture at Emirates Stadium. Arsenal coach, Unai Emery has disclosed that the club’s new signings, David Luiz, Nicolas Pepe, Dani Ceballos and Gabriel Martinelli are in contention to feature against Burnley. Emery could feature Mesut Ozil and Sead Kolasinac against the Clarets. Ozil and Kolasinac missed Arsenal’s 1-0 victory over Newcastle last weekend due to security issues. Arsenal’s provisional squad: Leno, Martinez, Maitland-Niles, Mustafi, Luiz, Sokratis, Chambers, Monreal, Kolasinac, Xhaka, Guendouzi, Torreira, Elneny, Willock, Ceballos, Mkhitaryan, Pepe, Ozil, Aubameyang, Lacazette, Martinelli. The kick-off time for the match is 12:30pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.